# Release & Deploy Workflow

Every time you package and push changes, follow ALL of these steps in order:

## 1. Bump version

Increment the patch version in `package.json` (e.g. `1.0.14` → `1.0.15`). Commit the version bump with a message like `v1.0.15: <short description>`.

## 2. Package

```powershell
npm run dist
```

## 3. Deploy locally

Extract the zip to the local EverQuest directory so the user runs the latest build:

```powershell
taskkill /F /IM p99-meter.exe 2>$null
Start-Sleep -Seconds 2
if (Test-Path "z:\Everquest P99\p99-meter") { Remove-Item "z:\Everquest P99\p99-meter" -Recurse -Force }
Expand-Archive -Path "z:\Everquest P99\AddOns\p99-meter\out\p99-meter-v<VERSION>.zip" -DestinationPath "z:\Everquest P99\" -Force
```

## 4. Push to git

```powershell
git push
```

## 5. Create GitHub release

Create a release with the zip attached and patch notes summarizing what changed:

```powershell
gh release create v<VERSION> "out/p99-meter-v<VERSION>.zip" --title "v<VERSION>" --notes "<patch notes>"
```

Patch notes should be concise bullet points describing user-facing changes.

**Do this automatically whenever you package and push — don't wait to be asked.**
